      "blocks": {
        "question_feaan3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are all exosome products the same?",
            "answer": "<p>No. The efficacy of exosome products depends on three critical factors: the source of the exosomes (stem cell-derived vs. plant-derived), the concentration per dose, and the delivery system that ensures they reach target cells intact. The CellRevive Exosome Cream uses the Endexome-EXO™ API, which delivers 4 billion stem cell-derived exosomes per dose in a lipid-compatible base of Avocado Oil, Safflower Oil, and Vitamin E that supports absorption and stability. Many commercial \"exosome\" products contain far lower concentrations or use plant-derived vesicles with limited signalling capability.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_P3DV8P": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What skin concerns does exosome cream target?",
            "answer": "<p>The CellRevive Exosome Cream targets the root biological mechanisms of ageing and skin damage:</p><ul><li><strong>Fine lines and wrinkles</strong> — exosomes signal fibroblasts to produce new collagen and elastin; clinical histology confirmed 100% of participants showed increased fibre density</li><li><strong>Loss of firmness</strong> — structural protein synthesis restores dermal density and resilience</li><li><strong>Dullness and uneven texture</strong> — accelerated cellular repair restores vitality and radiance</li><li><strong>Cellular ageing</strong> — statistically significant reduction in senescent cells (p=0.02) interrupts the inflammatory cascade that accelerates skin ageing</li><li><strong>Pigmentation</strong> — reduced chronic inflammation prevents new melanin overproduction; accelerated turnover clears existing pigmented cells</li></ul><p>Clinical testing showed 87.3% improvement in overall facial ageing signs.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What are exosomes in skincare?",
            "answer": "<p>Exosomes are microscopic extracellular vesicles — essentially biological communication carriers that cells use to send instructions to other cells. They carry proteins, lipids, and genetic information that direct cellular behaviour including repair, regeneration, and inflammation control. In skincare, exosomes signal skin cells to behave as they did when younger — stimulating collagen production, accelerating tissue repair, and reducing the accumulation of senescent (ageing) cells. The CellRevive Exosome Cream delivers 4 billion exosomes per dose via the proprietary Endexome-EXO™ API, making it one of the most concentrated topical exosome formulations available.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does exosome technology differ from regular moisturisers?",
            "answer": "<p>A moisturiser hydrates the skin's surface. The CellRevive Exosome Cream works at a fundamentally different level — it communicates with your skin cells, instructing them to repair, regenerate, and produce structural proteins. Clinical testing demonstrated 87.3% improvement in facial ageing signs, with 100% of participants showing histologically confirmed increases in both collagen and elastin. It also achieved a statistically significant reduction in senescent cells (p=0.02). While the cream does provide surface hydration through Sodium Hyaluronate (which holds 1,000x its weight in water), Avocado Oil, and Safflower Oil, its primary function is biological signalling — making it a regenerative treatment, not a cosmetic moisturiser.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who is the CellRevive Exosome Cream suitable for?",
            "answer": "<p>Anyone seeking advanced anti-ageing, skin repair, or regeneration beyond what standard actives deliver. It is particularly suited to those with visible signs of ageing (fine lines, loss of firmness, uneven tone), skin that has been exposed to cumulative UV or environmental damage, or anyone wanting to enhance the results of their existing protocol. Exosomes are biological messengers that work with the skin's natural signalling systems — clinical testing confirmed safety and tolerability for all skin types with no adverse reactions. It can be used alongside any Aliangé protocol as an enhancement step.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I use this within the Aliangé protocol?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Apply CellRevive after your serums and before your Day Cream SPF 15 (AM) or Ultimate A Night Cream (PM). The exosomes work best when applied to clean, serum-prepped skin — the serums deliver active ingredients while the exosome cream amplifies the skin's biological response to those actives. Use one pump (approximately 4 billion exosomes) and press gently into the skin. It can be used morning and evening, and is compatible with every Aliangé protocol.</p>"
          }
        },
